{% set basicTbodyCode %}<table>
  <caption>Quarterly Report</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Product</th>
      <th scope="col" data-numeric>Q1</th>
      <th scope="col" data-numeric>Q2</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Widget A</td>
      <td data-numeric>$12,500</td>
      <td data-numeric>$15,200</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Widget B</td>
      <td data-numeric>$8,900</td>
      <td data-numeric>$9,500</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tfoot>
    <tr>
      <td>Total</td>
      <td data-numeric>$21,400</td>
      <td data-numeric>$24,700</td>
    </tr>
  </tfoot>
</table>{% endset %}

{% set stripedCode %}<table class="striped">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">ID</th>
      <th scope="col">Name</th>
      <th scope="col">Status</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>001</td>
      <td>Project Alpha</td>
      <td>Active</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>002</td>
      <td>Project Beta</td>
      <td>Planning</td>
    </tr>
    <!-- More rows... -->
  </tbody>
</table>{% endset %}

{% set tbodyCss %}/* VB default hover state */
tbody tr:hover {
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
}

/* Striped variant — add .striped to the table */
table.striped tbody tr:nth-child(odd) {
  background: var(--color-surface-raised);
}{% endset %}

  <section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code> element contains one or more <a href="/docs/elements/native/tr/"><code>&lt;tr&gt;</code></a> elements that make up the data portion of a table. It should appear after <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a> and before <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a> in the source order.</p>
    <p>Vanilla Breeze applies a hover highlight on <code>tbody tr</code> rows using <code>var(--color-surface-raised)</code>, and supports a <code>.striped</code> variant that applies alternating background colors to odd rows for easier row tracking.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Every data table:</strong> All tables should use tbody to group data rows</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple tbody sections:</strong> Group related rows for visual or semantic separation (e.g., by department or category)</li>
      <li><strong>Dynamic content:</strong> JavaScript can target tbody directly for adding or removing rows without touching headers or footers</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>

    <h3>Basic Table with tbody</h3>
    <p>A complete table structure with <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a>, tbody, and <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a>. Hover over rows to see the built-in highlight.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-basic.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/basic" title="Basic table with hover rows" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Basic tbody example">{{ basicTbodyCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Striped Rows</h3>
    <p>Add <code>class="striped"</code> to the <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> element. VB alternates backgrounds on odd rows within tbody, making it easier to track data across wide tables.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-variants.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/variants" title="Striped table variant" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" label="Striped table">{{ stripedCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Row States</h3>
    <p>tbody rows can carry state information for visual indicators like selection or status.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-row-states.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/row-states" title="Table row states" shadow></browser-window>

    <h3>Density</h3>
    <p>Adjust cell padding for compact or spacious tables.</p>
    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-density.html" url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/table/density" title="Table density variants" shadow></browser-window>
  </section>

  <section>
